	Backend verifies signature â†’ updates DB â†’ status = paid

	Webhook is optional here â€” it may still trigger later, but your backend has already recorded payment.

Edge Case: User closes browser mid-payment or network fails

	Backend created order â†’ frontend opened Razorpay Checkout â†’ user pays

	Browser is closed or frontend never calls /verify

	Frontend does nothing

	Razorpay still processes payment â†’ triggers webhook

	Backend receives webhook â†’ verifies signature â†’ updates DB â†’ status = paid

	Webhook acts as a â€œsafety netâ€ ensuring your DB is consistent.

Key points / Interview-ready lines

	Frontend verification: fast, immediate, improves UX

	Webhooks: reliable, guarantees payment status even if frontend fails

	Backend DB always updated by either step 3 or step 4

	ğŸ’¡ Interview line you can say:

	â€œFrontend verification handles normal flow for immediate response, and webhooks handle edge cases where the user abandons the payment. Both use signature verification to ensure authenticity.â€

Optional note:

	Even in normal flow, webhook may still arrive later.

	Some companies ignore it if payment is already verified

